See an orthopaedic surgeon.  If your paediatrician or midwife recommends, it is a good idea to see an orthopaedic consultant to officially diagnose Developmental Dysplasia of the Hips in your baby and to agree on an appropriate treatment plan.

If the condition is severe in your baby's case, then a brace or cast (known as a hip spica) may be applied to the hip to help correct the position of your baby's hips and help them to heal correctly.

Your baby may require surgery in later life, but this is usually done once the hip bones are fully formed.{{Greenbox: Did you know?: If treated early, and if successful, a baby may grow up to have no further complications or issues with their hip and may even regain full mobility in their hips.}}
